@startuml Login_Sequence_Detailed
!theme blueprint
title Discord OAuth Login Flow with PKCE

actor User as U
participant "Frontend\n(blog.localtest.me:3000)" as FE
participant "Backend API\n(api.localtest.me:3001)" as BE
participant "Discord OAuth\n(discord.com)" as DC
database "PostgreSQL\nDatabase" as DB

== Phase 1: Login Initiation ==
U -> FE: 1. Click "Login with Discord"
note right: User initiates authentication

FE -> BE: 2. GET /auth/discord?lang=en
note right
**Request Details:**
- URL: api.localtest.me:3001/auth/discord
- Query: lang parameter for localization
- Method: GET (browser redirect)
end note

== Phase 2: Manual PKCE Generation ==
BE -> BE: 3. Generate security parameters

BE -> BE: 4. Store security values in cookies

== Phase 3: OAuth Authorization ==
BE -> DC: 5. Redirect to Discord OAuth

DC -> U: 6. Display authorization page

U -> DC: 7. Grant authorization
note right: User clicks "Authorize"

DC -> BE: 8. OAuth callback with authorization code
note right
**Callback Request:**
GET /auth/discord/callback
?code=AUTHORIZATION_CODE
&state=${state}|lang=en
end note

== Phase 4: Token Exchange with PKCE ==
BE -> BE: 9. Validate security parameters

alt State validation successful
    BE -> DC: 10. Exchange code for tokens (with PKCE)
    
    DC -> BE: 11. Return OAuth tokens
    note right
    **Response:**
    {
      "access_token": "ya29.a0AfH6...",
      "refresh_token": "1//04...",
      "expires_in": 3600,
      "token_type": "Bearer"
    }
    end note
else State validation failed
    BE -> FE: 11b. Redirect to error page
    note right: CSRF attack detected - abort
end

== Phase 5: User Profile & Database ==
BE -> DC: 12. Fetch user profile
note right
**GET https://discord.com/api/users/@me**
Authorization: Bearer ${access_token}
end note

DC -> BE: 13. Return user data
note right
**Discord User Object:**
{
  "id": "123456789",
  "email": "user@example.com",
  "username": "username",
  "global_name": "Display Name",
  "avatar": "hash",
  "discriminator": "0001"
}
end note

BE -> BE: 14. Process user data
note right
**Data Processing:**
1. Email validation & sanitization
2. Name sanitization  
3. Create avatar URL from Discord CDN
4. Prepare for database operations
end note

BE -> DB: 15. findOrCreateUser()

DB -> BE: 16. Return user record
note right
**User Object:**
{
  id: "uuid-v4",
  email: "user@example.com", 
  name: "Display Name",
  picture: "discord-avatar-url",
  provider: "discord",
  created_at: "timestamp",
  updated_at: "timestamp"
}
end note

== Phase 6: Session Creation ==
BE -> DB: 17. createSession()

DB -> BE: 18. Return session ID
note right
**Generated Session:**
- Session ID: random string
- Linked to user UUID
- Contains Discord tokens
- Expires in 1 hour
end note

== Phase 7: Cookie Management & Redirect ==
BE -> BE: 19. Set session cookie & cleanup
note right
**Cookie Operations:**
1. **Set Session Cookie:**
   - Name: "astral_session"
   - Value: session_id
   - Domain: .localtest.me
   - HttpOnly: true
   - MaxAge: 7 days

2. **Clear OAuth Cookies:**
   - discord_state (maxAge: 0)
   - discord_code_verifier (maxAge: 0)
end note

BE -> FE: 20. Redirect to frontend with language
note right
**Successful Redirect:**
Location: http://blog.localtest.me:3000?lang=en
**Cookie Header:**
Set-Cookie: astral_session=session_123; 
HttpOnly; Domain=.localtest.me; 
Path=/; Max-Age=604800
end note

== Phase 8: Authentication Verification ==
FE -> BE: 21. Verify authentication
note right
**GET /auth/me**
- Credentials: include (automatic cookie)
- No Authorization header needed
- Cookie-based authentication
end note

BE -> BE: 22. Extract session (Cookie Priority)

BE -> DB: 23. Validate session

alt Session valid
    DB -> BE: 24a. Return user data
    BE -> FE: 25a. Return authenticated user
    note right
    **Response:**
    {
      "user": {
        "id": "uuid",
        "email": "user@example.com",
        "name": "Display Name", 
        "picture": "avatar-url",
        "provider": "discord"
      }
    }
    end note
    
    FE -> U: 26a. Show authenticated interface
    note right: User sees logged-in state
else Session invalid/expired
    DB -> BE: 24b. No session found
    BE -> FE: 25b. Return authentication error
    FE -> U: 26b. Redirect to login
    note right: User must re-authenticate
end

@enduml
